---
import JournalEntry from '../../../layouts/JournalEntry.astro';
const base = (import.meta.env.BASE_URL || '').replace(/\/$/, '');
---

<JournalEntry
  title="Major Development Sprint – Tools, Encyclopedia, Slides, Concept Map Coach, Textbook Quizzes & Mobile Polish"
  date="2026-03-23"
  entryType="Development Log"
  course="D439 – Foundations of Nursing"
  showConceptMap={false}
>
  <p style="margin-bottom:1rem;">
    Today marked a major development sprint for the site. Over the course of the day,
    <strong>33 pull requests</strong> were opened, reviewed, and merged — spanning new
    interactive tools, encyclopedia articles, slide decks, layout improvements, bug fixes,
    mobile layout polish, and a full Foundations of Nursing textbook + quiz infrastructure.
    The work spans both the public WGU Nursing Tools section and the private study area.
  </p>

  <h2 style="font-size:1.2rem; font-weight:700; color:#1e293b; margin:1.5rem 0 0.75rem;">🛠️ New Tools</h2>

  <p style="margin-bottom:0.75rem;">
    <strong>Nursing Diagnosis Formulator</strong> (PR #26) — A fully interactive NANDA-I
    nursing diagnosis builder was added to the public
    <a href={`${base}/tools/nursing-diagnosis`} style="color:#6366f1; font-weight:600;">WGU Nursing Tools</a>
    section. Students can pick a diagnostic label, enter etiology and defining
    characteristics, set a SMART goal, add interventions with rationale, and record an
    evaluation. A live-formatted preview with print/export is included.
  </p>

  <p style="margin-bottom:0.75rem;">
    <strong>Concept Map Coach</strong> (PR #40) — A 7-phase, step-by-step coaching wizard
    was built to walk nursing students through the entire WGU Concept Map process —
    from data collection through evaluation. Each phase includes guided explanations,
    clinical prompts, and input fields. Completed maps can be shared via a compact JSON
    URL. The tool is available at the
    <a href={`${base}/tools/concept-map-coach`} style="color:#6366f1; font-weight:600;">Concept Map Coach</a>.
    Two follow-up PRs (#41, #44) fixed a module-scope button bug and restored
    Astro-scoped styles for JS-rendered elements using <code>:global()</code>.
  </p>

  <p style="margin-bottom:0.75rem;">
    <strong>Concept Map Case Library expansion</strong> (PR #27) — Twenty additional
    clinical case examples were added to the
    <a href={`${base}/tools/concept-map`} style="color:#6366f1; font-weight:600;">Clinical Concept Map</a>
    tool, bringing the library to <strong>36 fully populated sample cases</strong> covering
    common acute and chronic conditions encountered in clinical rotations.
  </p>

  <p style="margin-bottom:0.75rem;">
    <strong>Concept Map optional slide-deck view</strong> (PR #38) — The existing
    concept-map tool received an integrated horizontal-scrolling slide presentation view
    so students can walk through a concept map case in a structured, slide-by-slide format.
  </p>

  <p style="margin-bottom:1rem;">
    <strong>Interactive micro-quiz component</strong> (PR #54) — A self-contained,
    reusable quiz component was added at
    <a href={`${base}/tools/quiz`} style="color:#6366f1; font-weight:600;">/tools/quiz</a>.
    The proof-of-concept features a 3px progress bar, horizontally-sliding question carousel
    with smooth cubic-bezier transitions, pill-shaped answer options, and a two-region slide
    layout with a side panel that reveals feedback on answer. Designed as a template for
    embedding quizzes across the site.
  </p>

  <h2 style="font-size:1.2rem; font-weight:700; color:#1e293b; margin:1.5rem 0 0.75rem;">📚 New Encyclopedia Articles</h2>

  <ul style="margin-bottom:1rem; padding-left:1.5rem; line-height:1.9; color:#334155;">
    <li>
      <strong>Nursing Concept Map</strong> (PR #39) — A comprehensive reference article
      covering all 7 phases of the WGU Nursing Concept Map: Data Collection, Recognizing
      Cues, Analyzing Cues, Prioritized Hypotheses, Generated Solutions, Take Actions,
      and Evaluation of Outcomes. Read it in the
      <a href={`${base}/private/encyclopedia/nursing-concept-map`} style="color:#6366f1; font-weight:600;">Nursing Concept Map</a>
      encyclopedia article.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>COPD Exacerbation worked example</strong> (PR #42) — A fully completed
      Nursing Concept Map worked example for COPD exacerbation, added to the encyclopedia
      to model correct documentation for students. See the
      <a href={`${base}/private/encyclopedia/nursing-concept-map-copd-example`} style="color:#6366f1; font-weight:600;">COPD Exacerbation Concept Map</a>
      article.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Critical Reasoning</strong> (PR #33) — An article covering deductive,
      inductive, and abductive reasoning as applied methods of clinical inference.
      See the
      <a href={`${base}/private/encyclopedia/critical-reasoning`} style="color:#6366f1; font-weight:600;">Critical Reasoning</a>
      article.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Charcot Foot</strong> (PR #35) — A pathophysiology article on Charcot
      neuroarthropathy, including clinical presentation, risk factors, and nursing
      implications. See the
      <a href={`${base}/private/encyclopedia/charcot-foot`} style="color:#6366f1; font-weight:600;">Charcot Foot</a>
      article.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Spastic vs. Flaccid Paralysis</strong> (PR #36) — A comparative
      pathophysiology article distinguishing upper and lower motor neuron injuries.
      See the
      <a href={`${base}/private/encyclopedia/spastic-vs-flaccid-paralysis`} style="color:#6366f1; font-weight:600;">Spastic vs. Flaccid Paralysis</a>
      article.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>COPD Pathophysiology &amp; GOLD Classification</strong> (PR #47) — A
      graduate-level article covering the inflammatory cell infiltrate, protease–antiprotease
      imbalance, oxidative stress, emphysema subtypes, and the GOLD spirometric grading
      framework. See the
      <a href={`${base}/private/encyclopedia/copd-pathophysiology`} style="color:#6366f1; font-weight:600;">COPD Pathophysiology</a>
      article.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Encyclopedia Development Standards</strong> (PR #50) — A full authoring
      reference page was published at
      <a href={`${base}/private/encyclopedia/encyclopedia-standards`} style="color:#6366f1; font-weight:600;">Encyclopedia Standards</a>,
      documenting the three-pane layout, companion page requirements (slides &amp; summary),
      American English spelling, academic prose conventions, and inline bold paragraph
      heading style applied across all articles.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2 style="font-size:1.2rem; font-weight:700; color:#1e293b; margin:1.5rem 0 0.75rem;">🖼️ Slide Decks & Presentation Views</h2>

  <p style="margin-bottom:0.75rem;">
    <strong>Full-screen 2D slide layout</strong> (PR #37) — A new <code>SlidesLayout.astro</code>
    component was created to support full-screen, horizontally-scrolling 2D slide decks.
    A design-standards document was also published to <code>docs/slides-design-standards.md</code>
    to guide future slide authoring.
  </p>

  <p style="margin-bottom:0.75rem;">
    <strong>ADPIE slide presentation</strong> (PR #32) — A horizontal-scrolling slide deck
    covering the nursing process (ADPIE) was added to the private D439 study section.
    View it on the
    <a href={`${base}/private/d439/nursing-process-slides`} style="color:#6366f1; font-weight:600;">Nursing Process Slides</a>
    page.
  </p>

  <p style="margin-bottom:1rem;">
    <strong>Nursing Concept Map slides</strong> (PR #45) — A 13-column slide deck
    covering the full Nursing Concept Map article — including all 7 phases and a visual
    overview — was added to complement the new encyclopedia article. View it on the
    <a href={`${base}/private/encyclopedia/nursing-concept-map-slides`} style="color:#6366f1; font-weight:600;">Nursing Concept Map Slides</a>
    page.
  </p>

  <p style="margin-bottom:1rem;">
    <strong>COPD Exacerbation concept map slides</strong> (PR #53) — A companion slide
    deck for the COPD exacerbation worked example was added, walking through all 7 concept
    map phases in the horizontal-scrolling slide format. A "View as Slides" link was added
    to both the article header and the sidebar. View it on the
    <a href={`${base}/private/encyclopedia/nursing-concept-map-copd-example-slides`} style="color:#6366f1; font-weight:600;">COPD Exacerbation Concept Map Slides</a>
    page.
  </p>

  <h2 style="font-size:1.2rem; font-weight:700; color:#1e293b; margin:1.5rem 0 0.75rem;">🏗️ Private D439 Study Section</h2>

  <p style="margin-bottom:1rem;">
    <strong>D439 Foundations of Nursing private section</strong> (PR #30) — A new
    password-protected study area was created at the
    <a href={`${base}/private/d439`} style="color:#6366f1; font-weight:600;">D439 study section</a>
    with individual study modules for each major D439 topic: Assessment &amp; Vital Signs,
    Infection Control, Medications &amp; Procedures, Mobility &amp; Exercise,
    Nutrition &amp; Elimination, Hygiene &amp; Personal Care, Sleep, Comfort &amp; Pain,
    Wound &amp; Skin Care, Legal &amp; Ethical principles, Grief &amp; End-of-Life care,
    Communication &amp; Teaching, and Critical Thinking. The Nursing Process module
    (PR #32) received its own ADPIE slide presentation, and a Chain of Infection diagram
    (PR #34) was added to the Infection Control page.
  </p>

  <h2 style="font-size:1.2rem; font-weight:700; color:#1e293b; margin:1.5rem 0 0.75rem;">📖 Foundations of Nursing Textbook &amp; Quizzes</h2>

  <p style="margin-bottom:1rem;">
    <strong>Foundations of Nursing textbook + NCLEX quizzes</strong> (PR #52) — The
    full text of all five current Foundations of Nursing chapters was synced from the
    canonical <code>sagreenxyz/textbooks</code> source into the private study section.
    Interactive NCLEX-style chapter quizzes were created for each chapter:
    Chapter 1 (History and Evolution of Nursing), Chapter 2 (Legal, Ethical, and Professional
    Standards), Chapter 3 (Patient Rights, Advocacy, and Informed Consent),
    Chapter 4 (Therapeutic Communication), and Chapter 5 (Cultural Humility, Health
    Literacy, and Inclusive Care). The chapter index page received "Take Quiz" buttons
    and "Quiz Available" badges for all five chapters. The build grew from 70 to 75 pages.
  </p>

  <h2 style="font-size:1.2rem; font-weight:700; color:#1e293b; margin:1.5rem 0 0.75rem;">🎨 Layout &amp; UX Improvements</h2>

  <ul style="margin-bottom:1rem; padding-left:1.5rem; line-height:1.9; color:#334155;">
    <li>
      <strong>3-pane encyclopedia layout (TOC to right pane)</strong> (PR #46) — The
      Table of Contents was moved to a dedicated 220px right pane across all encyclopedia
      article pages, creating a standard three-column grid (240px left | 1fr content | 220px TOC).
      The right pane collapses at ≤1024px tablet breakpoint.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>SlidesLayout Astro CSS scoping fix</strong> (PR #49) — Slides were stacking
      vertically instead of scrolling horizontally due to Astro's scoped CSS failing to
      reach slot content from child components. Fixed by switching
      <code>SlidesLayout.astro</code> to <code>&lt;style is:global&gt;</code> so the
      structural layout CSS (<code>.slides-wrapper</code>, <code>.slide-column</code>,
      etc.) applies correctly.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Journal entry cleanup: opt-out concept map prop</strong> (PR #51) —
      <code>JournalEntry.astro</code> gained a <code>showConceptMap</code> boolean prop
      (default <code>true</code>) so development-log entries can suppress the WGU Nursing
      Concept Map template section that is only relevant to clinical entries.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Encyclopedia sidebar moved to left column</strong> (PR #31) — The Table of
      Contents / Quick Facts sidebar in encyclopedia articles was relocated from the right
      pane to the left for a more conventional reading layout.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Nursing Concept Map article TOC moved back to right</strong> (PR #43) — After
      review, the TOC in the new Nursing Concept Map article specifically was moved to
      the right pane for better readability given that article's structure.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Care plan print / PDF fix</strong> (PR #29) — The care plan print view was
      corrected to render as a professional paper form rather than a web page layout.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>npm CI lock-file sync fix</strong> (PR #28) — A dependency lock-file
      mismatch that broke the CI pipeline was resolved.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2 style="font-size:1.2rem; font-weight:700; color:#1e293b; margin:1.5rem 0 0.75rem;">🐛 Bug Fixes</h2>

  <p style="margin-bottom:0.75rem;">
    <strong>Quiz submit/reset button fix</strong> (PR #62) — Submit and reset buttons on
    the
    <a href={`${base}/private/d439/nursing-process`} style="color:#6366f1; font-weight:600;">Nursing Process</a>
    page and all chapter quiz pages were silently doing nothing. Astro bundles inline
    <code>&lt;script&gt;</code> tags as ES modules with deferred evaluation, so
    <code>getElementById</code> calls at module scope ran before the DOM was ready.
    Fixed by wrapping all DOM queries in a <code>DOMContentLoaded</code> listener across
    every affected page.
  </p>

  <h2 style="font-size:1.2rem; font-weight:700; color:#1e293b; margin:1.5rem 0 0.75rem;">📱 Mobile Layout</h2>

  <p style="margin-bottom:0.75rem;">
    <strong>Encyclopedia mobile redesign</strong> (PR #61) — All encyclopedia article
    pages received a mobile-first layout pass (≤768px breakpoint). Both the left topic
    panel and the right TOC sidebar are now hidden on phones so the full viewport width
    is given to the article content. At the tablet breakpoint (≤1024px) only the right
    TOC sidebar collapses. CSS is applied inline in each of the 23 article
    <code>.astro</code> files.
  </p>

  <h2 style="font-size:1.2rem; font-weight:700; color:#1e293b; margin:1.5rem 0 0.75rem;">📝 Additional Embedded Quiz</h2>

  <p style="margin-bottom:0.75rem;">
    <strong>ADPIE micro-quiz on the Nursing Process page</strong> (PR #60) — A
    12-question NCLEX-style micro-quiz covering the five ADPIE phases (Assessment,
    Diagnosis, Planning, Implementation, Evaluation) was embedded directly on the
    <a href={`${base}/private/d439/nursing-process`} style="color:#6366f1; font-weight:600;">Nursing Process</a>
    study page, using the same horizontally-sliding carousel introduced in the standalone
    <a href={`${base}/tools/quiz`} style="color:#6366f1; font-weight:600;">/tools/quiz</a>
    component.
  </p>

  <h2 style="font-size:1.2rem; font-weight:700; color:#1e293b; margin:1.5rem 0 0.75rem;">🔐 Security &amp; Access</h2>

  <p style="margin-bottom:0.75rem;">
    <strong>Daily-expiring per-page HMAC reveal links</strong> (PR #59) — A build-time
    HMAC token system was added to generate daily-expiring reveal links for individual
    private pages. Each link is signed with a secret key at build time and expires at
    midnight UTC, so shared links become invalid the following day. This provides a
    lightweight, no-backend way to share specific private pages with time-limited access
    without exposing the site-wide password.
  </p>

  <h2 style="font-size:1.2rem; font-weight:700; color:#1e293b; margin:1.5rem 0 0.75rem;">🖼️ Additional Slide Polish</h2>

  <p style="margin-bottom:1rem;">
    <strong>Hide legend panel on title &amp; final slides</strong> (PR #58) — The left
    legend panel that annotates slide columns was being rendered on the title slide and
    the closing summary slide, where it cluttered the layout. The panel is now hidden on
    both the first and last slides of every slide deck so those slides use the full
    horizontal width for their content.
  </p>

  <div style="margin-top:1.5rem; background:#eef2ff; border:1px solid #c7d2fe; border-radius:0.6rem; padding:1rem 1.25rem; font-size:0.875rem; color:#3730a3; display:flex; align-items:flex-start; gap:0.65rem;">
    <span style="font-size:1.1rem; flex-shrink:0;">🔗</span>
    <span>
      <strong>Cross-references:</strong> The tools documented above are available under
      <a href={`${base}/tools`} style="color:#4f46e5; font-weight:600;">WGU Nursing Tools</a>.
      The D439 private study section and encyclopedia are accessible from the
      <a href={`${base}/private/dashboard`} style="color:#4f46e5; font-weight:600;">private dashboard</a>
      after sign-in.
    </span>
  </div>
</JournalEntry>
